{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Government must conduct a \"fairness impact assessment\" of all future legislation",
        "additional_details": "According to Sir James Eadie QC \u201cParliament has no substantive, freestanding obligation to fairness\u201d and that \u201cIt is clear from case law that the enactment of Primary legislation carries with it no duty of fairness to the public\u201d. This is a quote from his submission to the judicial review into the equalization of the state pension age on 6 June 2019 at the High Court.",
        "background": "There is no \u201cDuty of Fairness\u201d in government legislation. It seems likely that this could detrimentally affect many people. The Government must conduct and publish a new analysis for each piece of primary legislation, showing how it will effect all groups in society. ",
